AB  - This paper constructs tests for autoregressive disturbances in a time series regression with missing observations, where the disturbance terms are generated by (i) an AR(1) process and (ii) an AR(p) process with a possible seasonal component. A point optimal invariant (POI) test is constructed for each problem. In addition, we show how to compute exact small sample p-values for the tests in O(n) operations, and give a computationally efficient procedure for choosing the specific alternative against which to make POI test most powerful invariant.
